    Page: 427
    Verse: 15
Tags:
  - Service
---
Perhaps the greatest service any man performs is not in the importance of
his work, but in the release of his inner powers. He makes a greater gift
to his fellow men in becoming a freed spirit than by a score of scientific
discoveries or hundreds of works of art.
